3 Download and Install

To install this package, start R (version “4.0.0”) and enter:

devtools::install_github("marziasettino/MMRFVariant", build_vignettes = TRUE)
library(MMRFVariant)

5 MMRFVariant Datasets

MMRF-CoMMpass data can be retrieved directly from MMRF-Commpass Researcher Gateway. They can be downloaded and imported as a dataframe into R environment.

MMRFVariant deals with the IA15 dataset (GRCh37 reference genome), which represents the ﬁfteen release of the complete baseline, available in a ﬂat ﬁle format (i.e. csv/txt) at the MMRF-RG.

With regard to the structure of IA15, it incorporates the following datasets:

MMRFVariant Datasets
  • MMRF_CoMMpass_IA15_PER_PATIENT: contains patient-clinical data such as demographic (e.g. age, gender, race, ethnicity) and cytogenetics (e.g. FISH results) information beside of the ISS disease stage for each patient;
  • MMRF_CoMMpass_IA15_STAND_ALONE_TRTRESP: contains the treatment-response information for each patient;
  • MMRF_CoMMpass_IA15a_All_Canonical_Variants: contains the variants annotations including the impact and eﬀect beside of the SIFT and Polyphen2 scores and the dbSNP Identiﬁers (IDs).

5.1 Fetching and importing MMRF-COMMPASS datasets

MMRFVariant requires a local copy of the MMRFCoMMpass datasets that can be downloaded from the MMRF-RG by the registered users. Once the datasets have been downloaded, they can be saved locally in a tab-delimited text ﬁle format for importing them into the R environment as described below.

patient <- read.csv("~/MMRF_CoMMpass_IA15_PER_PATIENT")

trt <- read.csv("~/MMRF_CoMMpass_IA15_STAND_ALONE_TRTRESP")

variant.ann <- read.csv("~/MMRF_CoMMpass_IA15a_All_Canonical_Variants")


6 Testing MMRFVariant functions

In order to test the MMRFVariant functions (without fetch MMRF-CoMMpass data from MMRF-RG), three fictitious datasets are provided in the “data” directory:

  • <variant.ann.example>
  • <patient.example>
  • <trt.example>
They replicate the original datasets format including only some fileds with respect to MMRF-CoMMpass datasets (.csv files) downloaded from MMRF-COMMPASS Research Gateway.

Annotated variant dataframe 
datatable(variant.ann.example,options = list(scrollX = TRUE, keys = TRUE))
Patient dataframe 
datatable(patient.example,options = list(scrollX = TRUE, keys = TRUE))
Treatment dataframe 
datatable(trt.example,options = list(scrollX = TRUE, keys = TRUE))
